markets.title: Will Solana have more trades than the NASDAQ on any day before Jan 1, 2026?
markets.rules_primary: If Solana has more trades than the NASDAQ on any day before Jan 1, 2026 according to flipthe.market, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: The comparison is based on daily trade counts as displayed on https://www.flipthe.market. Both Solana and NASDAQ must have complete day data for a valid comparison. If flipthe.market retroactively revises data, the revised data will be used only if the revision occurs before the deadline date. Partial day data does not count for resolution. If flipthe.market changes its methodology during the contract period, the new methodology applies going forward. In case flipthe.market is unavailable, fallback sources will be consulted in this order: official flipthe.market social media accounts (X/Twitter @flipthemarkt), the Solana Foundation, NASDAQ official statistics, Solscan.io, and Dune Analytics Solana dashboards. The market resolves to Yes as soon as Solana's daily trade count exceeds NASDAQ's on any single calendar day.
markets.early_close_condition: This market will close and expire early if Solana exceeds NASDAQ's daily trade count.
